Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 558 / 2005
of 12 April 2005
amending Regulation ( EEC ) No 3846 / 87 establishing a nomenclature of agricultural products for export refunds and Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 laying down specific implementing provisions for Council Regulation ( EEC ) No 804 / 68 with regard to export licences and export refunds in the milk and milk products sector
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Having regard to Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 of 17 May 1999 on the common organisation of the market in milk and milk products &#91; 1 &#93; , and in particular Article 31 ( 14 ) thereof ,
Considering the following reasons :
( 1 ) Commission Regulation ( EEC ) No 3846 / 87 &#91; 2 &#93; established the nomenclature of agricultural products for export refunds .
( 2 ) According to the reimbursement nomenclature , cheese shall be eligible for export refunds if they meet minimum requirements relating to dry milk mass and milk fat .
a type of cheese produced in certain new Member States could meet these requirements , but could not benefit from a refund because it does not fall under the current classification system of the export refund nomenclature .
Due to the importance of this cheese for the dairy industry , trade and the respective milk producers , it is appropriate to add a product code under the heading &quot; other cheeses &quot; so that the cheese can be included in the export refund nomenclature .
3 . The quantities for which export licences are applied for in the &apos; Cheese &apos; product category shall constantly exceed the profile of export restrictions applicable to the Community in accordance with the Convention on Agriculture concluded within the framework of the Uruguay Round multilateral trade negotiations .
the additional export licences requested under the newly created position will increase the pressure on this category .
4 . Pursuant to Article 3 of Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 &#91; 3 &#93; , no refund shall be granted for the export of cheese whose price is lower than EUR 230 per 100 kg before the application of the refund in the Member State of export .
However , this provision does not apply to cheese of code 0406 90 33 9919 of the nomenclature of export refunds .
In these circumstances , in view of the numerous applications for export licences for cheese , it is appropriate to apply this provision without exception to all types of cheese .
( 5 ) Pursuant to the footnote 10 in Annex I Sector 9 of Regulation ( EEC ) No 3846 / 87 applicable to grated cheese , cheese in powder form and processed cheese , non-milk components shall not be taken into account when calculating the refund .
this determination is to be extended to all types of cheese and the relevant foreign milk components are to be described in more detail .
for the exporter and even more so for the competent authority , it can be very difficult or even impossible to determine the weight of these components .
therefore , it is advisable to reduce the refund by a standard amount .
( 6 ) The refund shall be granted for the net weight of the cheese .
in cases where the cheese is wrapped in paraffin , ash or wax or wrapped in plastic foil , there may be ambiguity .
it must be envisaged that such an enclosure is not part of the net weight of the product for the purpose of calculating the refund .
for plastic film , paraffin and ash , it can be impossible for the exporter and the competent authority to determine the weight of these materials .
therefore , it is advisable to reduce the refund by a standard amount .
( 7 ) Regulations ( EEC ) No 3846 / 87 and ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 shall be amended accordingly .
( 8 ) The measures provided for in this Regulation are in line with the opinion of the Administrative Committee on Milk and Milk Products ;
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
Annex I to Regulation ( EEC ) No 3846 / 87 shall be amended in accordance with the Annex to this Regulation .
Article 2
Article 3 ( 4 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 shall be deleted .
Article 3
this Regulation shall enter into force on the day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union .
it applies to export licences which will be applied for from 27 May 2005 .
this Regulation is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 559 / 2005
of 12 April 2005
to initiate an investigation into the alleged circumvention of anti-dumping measures introduced by Council Regulation ( EC ) No 2074 / 2004 on imports of certain ring binder mechanisms originating in the People &amp; apos ; s Republic of China by imports of certain ring binder mechanisms sent from the Democratic People &amp; apos ; s Republic of Laos , whether or not registered as a source product of the Democratic People &amp; apos ; s Republic of Laos , and to record the latter imports in customs terms
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Having regard to Council Regulation ( EC ) No 384 / 96 of 22 December 1995 on the protection against dumped imports from non-European Community countries &#91; 1 &#93; ( hereinafter referred to as the &quot; Basic Regulation &quot; ) , in particular Articles 13 ( 3 ) , 14 ( 3 ) and 14 ( 5 ) thereof ,
after consulting the Advisory Committee ,
Considering the following reasons :
A. ANTRAG
1 . The Commission received an application pursuant to Article 13 ( 3 ) of the Basic Regulation to examine the alleged circumvention of anti-dumping measures against imports of certain ring binder mechanisms originating in the People &apos;s Republic of China ( hereinafter referred to as the &quot; People &apos;s Republic of China &quot; ) .
( 2 ) The application was submitted on 28 February 2005 by Ring Alliance Ringbuchtechnik GmbH on behalf of joint manufacturers , which accounts for more than 70 % of the joint production of certain ring binder mechanisms .
B. WARE
( 3 ) The goods affected by the alleged circumvention are certain ring binder mechanisms normally assigned to the KN ’ -@ code ex83051000 , originating in the People ’ s Republic of China .
this KN – @ code is only provided for information purposes .
( 4 ) The goods which are the subject of the investigation are certain ring binder mechanisms sent from the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Laos ( hereinafter referred to as &quot; examined goods &quot; ) and which are normally assigned to the same KN – @ code as the goods concerned originating in the People &apos;s Republic of China .
C. MONEY MEASURES
( 5 ) The measures currently in force and possibly adopted shall be a final anti-dumping duty introduced by Council Regulation ( EC ) No 2074 / 2004 &#91; 2 &#93; extending to imports of the same goods shipped from Vietnam &#91; 3 &#93; .
d . GREEN FOR SUPPORT
( 6 ) The application contains sufficient apparent evidence that the anti-dumping measures applicable to the goods concerned originating in the People &apos;s Republic of China are circumvented by reloading the examined goods in the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Laos and / or their assembly in the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Laos .
the following evidence was provided :
- According to the request , the trade structure has changed considerably due to a significant increase in imports of the goods examined , while imports of the goods concerned originating in the People &apos;s Republic of China declined after the introduction of measures for which there is otherwise no sufficient justification or justification other than the introduction of customs .
- This change in the trade structure seems to be due to the transfer of certain ring binder mechanics originating in the People &apos;s Republic of China to the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Laos and / or the assembly of certain ring binder mechanics in the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Laos .
- In addition , the application contains sufficient evidence that the remedy effect of the anti-dumping measures applicable to the goods concerned originating in the People &apos;s Republic of China is undermined both in terms of quantity and prices .
It appears that significant quantities of imports of certain ring binder mechanisms from the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Laos have replaced the imports of the goods concerned originating in the People &apos;s Republic of China .
- In addition , there is sufficient evidence that the examined goods are sold at prices that have dumped compared to the normal value originally determined for certain ring binder mechanics originating in the People &apos;s Republic of China .
- Should other circumvention practices within the meaning of Article 13 of the Basic Regulation be established in the course of the investigation in addition to dispatch via the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Laos , the investigation may also extend to these practices .
E. PROCEDURE
7 . For the above reasons , the Commission has concluded that the evidence is sufficient to justify the opening of an investigation in accordance with Article 13 of the Basic Regulation and to cover customs imports from certain ring binder mechanisms sent from the Democratic People &amp; apos ; s Republic of Laos , irrespective of whether their origin is indicated in the application with the Democratic People &amp; apos ; s Republic of Laos , in accordance with Article 14 ( 5 ) of the Basic Regulation .
a ) Questionnaire
( 8 ) In order to obtain the information it deems necessary for its investigation , the Commission shall send questionnaires to the exporters / manufacturers and their associations in the Democratic People &amp; apos ; s Republic of Laos , to the exporters / manufacturers and their associations in the People &amp; apos ; s Republic of China and to the importers and their Community associations involved in the investigation leading to the measures in force or mentioned in the application , as well as to the authorities of the People &amp; apos ; s Republic of China and the authorities in the Democratic People &amp; apos ; s Republic of Laos .
information may also be obtained from the Community industry .
9 . All interested parties should promptly and within the time limit laid down in Article 3 ask the Commission whether they are mentioned in the request and , where appropriate , request a questionnaire within the time limit set in Article 3 ( 1 ) of this Regulation , since the time limit set in Article 3 ( 2 ) of this Regulation applies to all interested parties .
( 10 ) The authorities of the People &apos;s Republic of China and the authorities in the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Laos shall be informed of the opening of the investigation and shall receive a copy of the application .
b ) Obtaining information and hearings
( 11 ) All interested parties shall be invited to present their position in writing on presentation of relevant evidence .
the Commission may also consult interested parties where requested by the parties in writing and demonstrate that there are specific reasons for their hearing .
c ) exemption from customs registration of imports or from measures
12 . As the alleged circumvention takes place outside the Community , manufacturers of the goods concerned may , in accordance with Article 13 ( 4 ) of the Basic Regulation which can prove that they are not connected with a manufacturer subject to the measures in force and for which it has been established that they are not involved in the circumvention practices within the meaning of Article 13 ( 1 ) and ( 2 ) of the Basic Regulation , be exempted from the customs registration of imports or from the measures .
Manufacturers wishing to obtain exemption should submit an application by appropriate evidence within the time limit set in Article 3 ( 3 ) .
F. CUSTOMS ADOPTION
13 . Pursuant to Article 14 ( 5 ) of the Basic Regulation , imports of the goods examined should be duty-amiced so that , in the case in which a circumvention is established during the investigation , anti-dumping duties may be levied retroactively from the time of customs registration on imports sent from the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Laos in the appropriate amount .
g . FRISTS
( 14 ) In the interest of proper administration , deadlines should be set within which
- interested parties can contact the Commission themselves , present their position in writing and provide answers to the questionnaire or other information to be taken into account in the investigation ;
- manufacturers in the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Laos may request exemption from customs registration of imports or measures ;
- interested parties may submit a written request for consultation by the Commission .
( 15 ) It is pointed out that the exercise of most of the procedural rights enshrined in the Basic Regulation presupposes that the party concerned shall itself register within the time limit specified in Article 3 .
h . NOT WORK
16 . If an interested party refuses access to the necessary information or fails to provide it within the time limits set or significantly impedes the investigation , positive or negative findings may be made on the basis of the available information in accordance with Article 18 of the Basic Regulation .
17 . Where it is established that an interested party has provided untrue or misleading information , such information shall not be taken into account ; the available information may be used in accordance with Article 18 of the Basic Regulation .
If an interested party does not cooperate , or only in part , and the findings are therefore based on the available information in accordance with Article 18 of the basic regulation , this may lead to a result that is less favourable for that party than if it had worked with it -
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
Ring binder mechanisms within the meaning of this regulation are mechanics consisting of two rectangular steel rails or steel wires with at least four brackets made of steel wire attached to them and held together by means of a steel cover .
they can be opened either by pulling the half rings apart or with a small steel printing mechanism attached to the ring binder mechanism .
Article 2
Customs authorities are instructed under Article 13 ( 3 ) and Article 14 ( 5 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 384 / 96 to take appropriate steps to cover customs imports into the Community referred to in Article 1 of this Regulation .
Customs registration ends nine months after the entry into force of this Regulation .
the Commission may instruct customs authorities by regulation to cease customs registration of imports of goods into the Community produced by exporters who have requested exemption from customs registration and for whom it has been established that they do not circumvent anti-dumping duties .
Article 3
( 1 ) The questionnaires shall be requested from the Commission within 15 days of the publication of this Regulation in the Official Journal of the European Union .
( 2 ) Unless otherwise specified , interested parties must contact the Commission within 40 days of publication of this announcement in the Official Journal of the European Union , state their position in writing and submit their replies to the questionnaire and other information if such information is to be taken into account in the investigation .
( 3 ) Manufacturers in the Democratic People &apos;s Republic of Laos who wish to apply for exemption from customs registration of imports or measures should submit an application by appropriate evidence within the same period of 40 days .
( 4 ) Within the same period of 40 days , interested parties may also submit an application for consultation by the Commission .
( 5 ) All relevant information , requests for consultation or requirements of a questionnaire as well as all requests for exemption from the customs registration of imports or from the measures shall be transmitted by the interested parties in writing ( not in electronic form , unless otherwise specified ) , stating name , address , e-mail address , telephone , fax and / or telex numbers .
all written opinions , including the information requested in this Regulation , responses to the questionnaire and all letters sent by interested parties on a confidential basis , must bear the note &quot; For limited use &quot; &#91; 4 &#93; and be transmitted in accordance with Article 19 ( 2 ) of the Basic Regulation together with a non-confidential version bearing the note &quot; For inspection by interested parties &quot; .
European Commission
Directorate-General for Trade
Directorate B
Office : j ’ -@ 79 5 / 16
b • -@ 1049 Brussels
Fax ( 32 – 2 ) 295 65 05 .
Article 4
this Regulation shall enter into force on the day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union .
this Regulation is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
Council Regulation ( EC ) No 560 / 2005
of 12 April 2005
on the application of specific restrictive measures against certain persons and organisations in view of the situation in the Republic of Côte d &apos;Ivoire
the COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community , in particular Articles 60 , 301 and 308 ,
Having regard to Council Common Position 2004 / 852 / CFSP of 13 December 2004 on restrictive measures against the Republic of Côte d &apos;Ivoire &#91; 1 &#93; ,
on a proposal from the Commission ,
Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament &#91; 2 &#93; ,
Considering the following reasons :
( 1 ) Disapproving the resumption of hostilities in Côte d &apos;Ivoire and the repeated violations of the ceasefire agreements of 3 May 2003 , the United Nations Security Council , in accordance with Chapter VII of the United Nations Charter of 15 November 2004 , decided in its Resolution 1572 ( 2004 ) to impose restrictive measures on Côte d &apos;Ivoire .
( 3 ) These measures shall fall within the scope of the Treaty and shall therefore require Community legislation to the extent that they concern the territory of the Community , so as not to distort competition .
for the purposes of this Regulation , the territory of the Community shall be the entirety of the territories of the Member States to which the Treaty shall apply in accordance with its provisions .
4 . In order to ensure the effectiveness of the measures provided for in this Regulation , this Regulation should enter into force on the date of its publication .
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
for the purposes of this Regulation , the term
1 .
&quot; Sanctions Committee &quot; the United Nations Security Council Committee pursuant to point 14 of United Nations Security Council Resolution 1572 ( 2004 ) ;
2 . &quot; Money &quot; financial assets and economic benefits of any kind , including but not limited to :
a ) cash , checks , monetary claims , bills of exchange , payment orders and other means of payment ;
( b ) deposits with financial institutions or other entities , funds on accounts , payment entitlements and securitised receivables ;
( c ) publicly and non-publicly traded securities and debt securities , including shares and shares , securities certificates , long-term and short / medium term bonds , warrants , bonds and derivative contracts ;
( d ) interest income , dividends or other income or value gains from assets ;
e ) loans , rights to offsetting , guarantees , contractual performance guarantees or other financial claims ;
f ) letters of credit , knots , certificates of transfer ;
( g ) documents on securitisation of shares in fund assets or other financial resources ;
( h ) other export financing instruments ;
3. &quot; freezing funds &quot; prevents any form of movement , transfer , alteration and use of funds , as well as access to them or their use , thereby altering the volume , amount , value , property , possession , characteristics or purpose of the funds , or other changes that allow the use of funds , including asset management ;
4. &quot; economic resources &quot; assets of any kind , whether material or immaterial , movable or immovable , which are not funds but which can be used to purchase funds , goods or services ;
&quot; Freezing economic resources &quot; means preventing the use of economic resources for the acquisition of funds , goods or services , which also includes the sale , leasing or pledging of these resources , but is not limited to them .
Article 2
( 1 ) All funds and economic resources belonging to the natural or legal persons or organisations listed in Annex I or subject to their direct or indirect control shall be frozen .
( 2 ) The natural or legal persons or organisations listed in Annex I may not be made available or benefit directly or indirectly from funds or economic resources .
( 3 ) The knowledgeable and deliberate participation in activities whose purpose or effect consists indirectly or indirectly in circumventing the measures referred to in paragraphs 1 and 2 is prohibited .
Article 3
Notwithstanding Article 2 , the competent authorities of the Member States listed in Annex II may , if they have previously informed the Sanctions Committee of their intention to authorise access to these funds and economic resources and have not received a relevant communication from the Sanctions Committee within two working days , authorise the release or provision of certain frozen funds or economic resources under the conditions that appear appropriate to them if they have found that these funds or economic resources
( a ) are necessary for basic expenditure , including payment of food , rents or mortgages , medicines and medical treatment , taxes , insurance premiums and fees for public utilities ;
( b ) serve exclusively to pay reasonable fees and reimburse expenses related to the provision of legal services ;
c ) serve exclusively to pay fees or costs for the routine custody or management of frozen funds or economic resources .
Notwithstanding Article 2 , the competent authorities of the Member States listed in Annex II may authorise the release or provision of certain frozen funds or economic resources if they have previously established that the funds or economic resources are necessary to cover extraordinary expenditure , provided that they have informed the Sanctions Committee of this finding and the Sanctions Committee has approved this finding in accordance with point 14 ( e ) of Resolution 1572 ( 2004 ) of the UN Security Council .
Article 4
Notwithstanding Article 2 , the competent authorities of the Member States listed in Annex II may authorise the release of certain funds or economic resources if the following conditions are met :
( a ) funds or economic resources shall be the subject of a lien or decision of a court , administrative body or arbitral tribunal before 15 November 2004 ;
( b ) the funds or economic resources shall be used solely for the fulfilment of claims secured by such a lien or recognised as enforceable by such a decision , in compliance with the laws and laws governing the rights of persons asserting such claims ;
( c ) the lien or decision does not favour a person or organisation listed in Annex I ;
( d ) the recognition of the lien or decision does not conflict with the public order of the Member State concerned ;
( e ) the competent authority has brought to the attention of the Sanctions Committee the lien or decision .
Article 5
the competent authority concerned shall inform the competent authorities of the other Member States and the Commission of any authorisation granted under Article 3 or Article 4 .
Article 6
Article 2 paragraph 2 does not apply to credit - on frozen accounts - from
a ) interest or other income from frozen accounts , or
( b ) payments due on the basis of contracts , agreements or obligations made or incurred before the date from which these accounts are subject to this Regulation ;
provided that these interest , other income and payments are frozen in accordance with Article 2 ( 1 ) .
Article 7
Article 2 ( 2 ) does not prevent financial institutions from crediting funds transferred to them by third parties for credit to the account of persons or organisations listed in Annex I , provided that such credits are also frozen into frozen accounts .
financial institutions shall inform the competent authorities immediately of such transactions .
Article 8
( 1 ) Without prejudice to the provisions applicable to reporting , confidentiality and professional secrecy and Article 284 of the Treaty , natural and legal persons , organisations and bodies shall be obliged to :
( a ) Immediately provide to the competent authorities of the Member States in which they are established or established all information which would facilitate compliance with this Regulation , such as accounts and credits frozen in accordance with Article 2 , and to transmit the information in question to the Commission either directly or through these competent authorities ;
( b ) cooperate with the competent authorities listed in Annex II when reviewing this information .
( 2 ) Additional information sent directly to the Commission shall be made available to the competent authorities of the Member States concerned .
3 . The information transmitted or received under this Article may only be used for the purposes for which it was transmitted or received .
Article 9
neither the natural or legal persons or organisations that freeze money and economic resources or refuse to provide such funds or economic resources , nor their directors or employees who have acted in the belief that such measures are in line with this Regulation , may be held liable in any way , unless the freezing of funds and economic resources is proven to be due to negligence .
Article 10
the Commission and the Member States shall inform each other without delay of the measures taken under this Regulation and shall exchange further relevant information available to them in connection with this Regulation , in particular information on infringements , problems of enforcement and judgments by national courts .
Article 11
the Commission is empowered to :
( a ) amend Annex I on the basis of the decisions of the Sanctions Committee ; and
( b ) amend Annex II on the basis of information provided by Member States .
Article 12
Member States shall lay down rules on sanctions for infringements of this Regulation and shall take all necessary measures to enforce these sanctions .
the sanctions envisaged must be effective , proportionate and dissuasive .
Member States shall notify the Commission of these rules without delay after the entry into force of this Regulation and shall inform it of any subsequent amendments .
Article 13
this Regulation applies
( a ) in the Community territory , including its airspace ;
( b ) on board the aircraft or vessels subject to the jurisdiction of a Member State ;
( c ) for persons nationality of a Member State within or outside the Community territory ;
( d ) for legal persons , groups or organisations established or registered under the law of a Member State ;
e ) for any legal entity , group or organization engaged in business within the community .
Article 14
this Regulation shall enter into force on the date of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union .
it is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 561 / 2005
of 13 April 2005
to set lump-sum import values for determining import prices in the fruit and vegetable sector
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Having regard to Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 3223 / 94 of 21 December 1994 implementing provisions on the import regime for fruit and vegetables &#91; 1 &#93; , and in particular Article 4 ( 1 ) thereof ,
Considering the following reasons :
1 . The criteria to be determined by the Commission for determining the lump-sum import values in application of the results of the Uruguay @ Round multilateral trade negotiations shall be laid down in Regulation ( EC ) No 3223 / 94 for the products and periods listed in its Annex .
2 . In application of the above criteria , the lump-sum import values indicated in the Annex to this Regulation shall be taken into account ;
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
the lump-sum import values referred to in Article 4 of Regulation ( EC ) No 3223 / 94 are laid down in the table in the Annex to this Regulation .
Article 2
this Regulation will enter into force on 14 April 2005 .
this Regulation is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 562 / 2005
of 5 April 2005
with implementing provisions of Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 as regards mutual communications from Member States and the Commission in the milk and milk products sector
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Having regard to Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 of 17 May 1999 on the common organisation of the market in milk and milk products &#91; 1 &#93; , and in particular Article 40 thereof ,
Considering the following reasons :
( 1 ) Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 1498 / 1999 of 8 July 1999 laying down implementing provisions for Council Regulation ( EEC ) No 804 / 68 as regards mutual communications from Member States and the Commission in the milk and milk products sector &#91; 2 &#93; has repeatedly been amended on essential points .
a number of amendments have been introduced to Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 and all regulations with implementing provisions .
For reasons of clarity , it is therefore advisable to repeal Regulation ( EC ) No 1498 / 1999 and replace it with a new regulation .
( 2 ) Regular communications on the functioning of the intervention measures provided for in Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 and , in particular , on the development of the stocks of the products concerned at intervention points or in private warehouses shall be essential for the assessment of production and the market in the milk and milk products sector .
3 . The fixing of aid for skimmed milk processed into casein and refunds is only possible on the basis of communications on the development of domestic and world market prices .
4 . Accurate and regular monitoring of trade flows , which may assess the impact of refunds , shall require information on exports of the products for which refunds are set , in particular as regards the quantities for which the surcharge is awarded under a tender .
( 5 ) In order to comply with the obligations arising from the Convention on Agriculture ( hereinafter : &apos; Convention on Agriculture &apos; ) concluded within the framework of the multilateral trade negotiations of the Uruguay @ Round , approved by Council Decision 94 / 800 / EC &#91; 3 &#93; , additional and more precise information on imports and exports , in particular on the application for licences and their use , is required .
rapid information on the development of exports is necessary for the best possible use .
under the same Convention , exports under food aid are not subject to the constraints imposed on subsidised exports .
Therefore , notifications of export licence applications must be distinguished as to whether these are notifications of licences requested for food aid deliveries .
( 6 ) Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 of 26 January 1999 laying down specific implementing provisions for Council Regulation ( EEC ) No 804 / 68 as regards export licences and export refunds in the milk and milk products sector &#91; 4 &#93; contains specific provisions for exports of certain milk products to Canada , the United States and the Dominican Republic .
therefore , the transmission of the relevant information must be provided .
( 7 ) Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 provides for a special scheme for the granting of refunds for components originating in the Community and used for the production of processed cheese in the context of active processing .
therefore , the transmission of the relevant information must be provided .
( 8 ) Pursuant to Article 5 of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 , in certain cases an export licence may also apply to a product code other than the code specified in field 16 of the export licence .
therefore , the transmission of the relevant information must be provided .
( 9 ) In accordance with Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 2535 / 2001 of 14 December 2001 laying down implementing provisions to Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 on the import regime for milk and milk products and on the opening of the relevant tariff quotas &#91; 5 &#93; , certificates IMA 1 shall be issued by the competent authorities in third countries to manage certain import quotas .
Member States shall notify the Commission of the quantities of products for which import licences are granted on the basis of IMA 1 certificates .
Experience has shown that these notifications do not always make it possible to closely monitor the progress of imports in their individual phases .
therefore , the transmission of additional information must be provided .
( 10 ) The experience gained over the years in evaluating the information transmitted has shown that this information is often transmitted too frequently .
therefore , the frequency of certain communications must be reduced .
( 11 ) It is essential to be able to compare price quotations for products , in particular for the purpose of calculating refunds and aid contributions .
Furthermore , the plausibility of these price quotations must be explained by weighting the information .
( 12 ) The means of communication have developed a lot in recent years .
this development must be taken into account in order to make the communications faster , more efficient and safer .
( 13 ) The measures provided for in this Regulation are in line with the opinion of the Administrative Committee on Milk and Milk Products ;
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Chapter I
Inventories AND INTERVENTION MEASURES
Article 1
With regard to the intervention measures taken in accordance with Article 6 ( 1 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 , Member States shall provide the Commission with the following information no later than 10 of each month for the previous month :
( a ) the quantities of butter in stock at the end of the month in question and the quantities of butter stored and outsourced during the month in question in accordance with the sample in Part A of Annex I to this Regulation ;
( b ) the quantities of butter outsourced during the month in question , broken down by the rules applicable to them , in accordance with the model in Part B of Annex I to this Regulation ;
( c ) the age structure of butter quantities in stock at the end of the month in question in accordance with the model in Part C of Annex I to this Regulation .
With regard to the intervention measures taken in accordance with Article 6 ( 3 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 , Member States shall , at the latest on the 10th of each month for the previous month , provide the following information in accordance with the model in Annex II to this Regulation :
( a ) the amount of butter stored and outsourced during the month in question and the amount of cream converted into butter equivalent ;
( b ) the total amount of butter in stock at the end of the month in question and the amount of cream converted into butter equivalent .
Article 2
With regard to the intervention measures taken in accordance with Article 7 ( 1 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 , Member States shall provide the Commission with the following information no later than the 10th of each month for the previous month :
( a ) the quantities of skimmed milk powder in stock at the end of the month in question and the quantities stored and outsourced during the month in question in accordance with the sample in Part A of Annex III to this Regulation ;
( b ) the quantities of skimmed milk powder outsourced during the month in question , broken down by the rules applicable to them , in accordance with the model in Part B of Annex III to this Regulation ;
( c ) the age structure of the quantities of skimmed milk powder in stock at the end of the month in question in accordance with the pattern in Part C of Annex III to this Regulation .
Article 3
With regard to the intervention measures taken in accordance with Articles 8 and 9 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 , Member States shall , at the latest on the 10th of each month for the previous month , provide the following information in accordance with the model in Annex IV to this Regulation :
( a ) the quantities of cheese stored and outsourced during the month in question , broken down by cheeses ;
b ) the quantities of cheese in stock at the end of the month in question , broken down by cheeses .
Article 4
in the sense of this chapter are :
a ) &quot; stored quantities &quot; : the quantities taken over by the intervention body and not taken over in stock ;
b ) &quot; outsourced quantities &quot; : the quantities withdrawn or - if the takeover by the buyer takes place before the withdrawal - the quantities taken over .
Chapter II
AID MEASURES FOR skimmed milk and skimmed milk powder
Article 5
With regard to the aid granted in accordance with Article 11 ( 1 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 for skimmed milk and skimmed milk powder used for feed purposes , the Member States shall , at the latest on the 20th of each month for the previous month , provide the following information in accordance with the model set out in Annex V to this Regulation :
( a ) the quantities of skimmed milk used to produce compound feed for which aid was requested during the month in question ;
( b ) the quantities of denatured skimmed milk powder for which aid has been requested during the month in question ;
( c ) the skimmed milk powder quantities used to produce compound feedingstuffs for which aid was requested during the month in question .
2 . With regard to the aid granted under Article 12 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 for skimmed milk processed into casein , the Member States shall , at the latest on the 20th of each month for the previous month , in accordance with the model in Annex V to this Regulation , transmit to the Commission the quantities of skimmed milk for which aid was requested during the previous month .
these quantities are broken down according to the quality of the casein or caseinates produced .
Chapter III
Prices
Article 6
Member States shall notify the Commission no later than 11.00 a.m. ( Brussels time ) on Wednesday of each week of the prices from the factory applied on their territory last week for the products referred to in Annex VI .
Member States shall notify prices reported by market participants for dairy products , other than cheese , if national production is 2 % or more in line with Community production or if production at national level is considered representative by the competent national authority .
for cheese , Member States shall notify prices by cheeses equivalent to 8 % or more of total national cheese production .
Member States shall notify the Commission of the crude milk prices paid to producers on their territory no later than one month after the end of the previous month .
these prices are expressed as weighted means determined on the basis of surveys by the authority of the Member State .
Member States shall take the necessary measures to ensure that their communications on prices in force in the Community are representative , realistic and complete .
To this end , Member States submit an annual report to the Commission by 31 May using the standard questionnaire in Annex XII .
Member States shall take the necessary measures to ensure that the market participants concerned provide them with the necessary information within the relevant time limits .
( 5 ) The price from the factory within the meaning of this article is the price at which the product is purchased from the company , excluding taxes ( VAT ) and other costs ( transport , loading , internal transport , treatment , storage , pallets , insurance , etc . ) .
the price is expressed as a weighted means determined on the basis of surveys by the authority of the Member State .
Chapter IV
Trade
Section 1
Imports
Article 7
Member States shall inform the Commission of :
1. at the latest one month after the start of the quota year for the previous quota year , the quantities of products for which import licences were granted within the framework of the quotas of Article 5 of Regulation ( EC ) No 2535 / 2001 are broken down by KN ’ -@ codes and codes of the countries of origin ;
2. on 10 January or 10 July at the latest for the six preceding months , the quantities of products for which import licences were granted within the framework of the quotas laid down in Article 24 of Regulation ( EC ) No 2535 / 2001 shall be broken down by KN ’ -@ codes and codes of the countries of origin ;
3. on the 10th of each month for the previous month at the latest , the quantities of products for which import licences have been granted to which the non-preferential tariffs provided for in the Common Customs Tariff apply are broken down by KN ’ -@ codes and codes of the countries of origin ;
4. on the 10th of each month for the previous month at the latest the quantities of products for which import licences for imports have been granted in accordance with Article 1 of Council Regulation ( EC ) No 2007 / 2000 &#91; 6 &#93; and Article 10 of the Interim Agreement on Trade and Trade Issues between the European Community on the one hand and the Lebanese Republic on the other , approved by Council Decision 2002 / 761 / EC &#91; 7 &#93; , broken down by KN ’ -@ codes and codes of the countries of origin ;
5. on the 10th of each month for the previous month at the latest , the quantities of products for which import licences were granted under the quotas laid down in Article 20 of Regulation ( EC ) No 2535 / 2001 , broken down by KN ’ -@ codes and codes of the countries of origin ;
6. once a year , at the latest three months after expiry of each quota period , the unused quantities of licences granted under the import quotas in accordance with Regulation ( EC ) No 2535 / 200 , broken down by quota numbers , KN – @ codes and codes of the countries of origin .
where appropriate , Member States shall inform the Commission that no licences have been granted for the reference periods concerned .
Article 8
Member States shall transmit to the Commission , no later than 31 March , for the previous year , in accordance with the model set out in Annex VII , the following information broken down by KN ’ -@ codes on import licences granted upon presentation of a certificate IMA 1 in accordance with Title 2 Chapter III of Regulation ( EC ) No 2535 / 2001 , stating the number of certificate IMA 1 :
( a ) the quantity of products for which the import licence was granted and the date of licensing ;
( b ) the quantity of products for which safety has been released .
Section 2
Exports
Article 9
Member States shall notify the Commission of :
( a ) the quantities broken down according to the codes of the export refund nomenclature for milk products and the identification codes for which licences were applied for on the same day
I ) in accordance with Article 1 of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 , except licences in accordance with Article 17 of that Regulation ,
II ) in accordance with Article 17 of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 ;
( b ) where appropriate , that no licences have been applied for in accordance with point ( a ) on the same day ;
( c ) the quantities broken down by applications , the codes of export refund nomenclature for milk products and identification codes for which provisional licences were requested on the same day in accordance with Article 8 of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 , stating :
I ) the tender period , accompanied by a copy of the document confirming the invitation to tender for the requested quantities ,
II ) the quantities of products to which the tender relates or , in the case of a tender by armed forces pursuant to Article 36 ( 1 ) ( c ) of Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 800 / 1999 &#91; 8 &#93; , where the exact quantity is not specified , the approximate quantity broken down as described above ;
( d ) the quantities broken down by codes of export refund nomenclature for milk products and by identification codes for which provisional licences were finally granted or annulled on the same day in accordance with Article 8 of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 , stating the tendering body and the date and quantity of the provisional licence in accordance with the model in Part A of Annex VIII to this Regulation ;
( e ) where appropriate , the redefined quantity of products to which the invitation to tender referred in accordance with point ( c ) , in accordance with the model in Part A of Annex VIII to this Regulation ;
( f ) the quantities broken down by country and by codes of export refund nomenclature for dairy products for which final licences have been granted in accordance with Articles 20 and 20a of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 , as defined in Part B of Annex VIII to this Regulation .
With regard to the communication referred to in paragraph 1 ( c ) ( 1 ) , one communication per Member State shall be sufficient if several applications have been submitted for the same invitation to tender .
Member States shall not notify on a daily basis the quantities for which export licence applications have been submitted in accordance with the second subparagraph of Article 1 ( 1 ) and Articles 18 , 20 and 20a of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 and for which no refund has been requested or which are intended for food aid deliveries within the meaning of Article 10 ( 4 ) of the Convention on Agriculture concluded within the framework of the Uruguay @ Round .
Article 10
Member States shall inform the Commission on Monday of each week for the previous week of the quantities broken down by codes of the export refund nomenclature for milk products , for which applications for licences have been submitted in accordance with the second subparagraph of Article 1 ( 1 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 and no refund has been requested , in accordance with the model set out in Part C of Annex VIII to this Regulation .
Article 11
Member States shall provide the Commission with the following information before the 16th of each month for the previous month :
( a ) the quantities broken down by codes of the export refund nomenclature for milk products for which licence applications have been annulled in accordance with Article 10 ( 3 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 , stating the refund rate , in accordance with the model in Part A of Annex IX to this Regulation ;
( b ) the quantities broken down by codes of the export refund nomenclature for milk products which were not exported after the licences in question became invalid , stating the refund rate , in accordance with the model in Part B of Annex IX to this Regulation ;
( c ) the quantities broken down by code of the export refund nomenclature for milk products and identification codes for which export licences for deliveries under food aid have been requested in accordance with Article 10 ( 4 ) of the Uruguay – @ Round Convention on Agriculture , as set out in Part C of Annex IX to this Regulation ;
( d ) the quantities of milk products broken down in accordance with KN ’ -@ codes and codes of the country of origin , to which none of the legal situations referred to in Article 23 ( 2 ) of the Treaty apply and which are introduced for the manufacture of products of KN ’ -@ Code 040630 , in accordance with Article 11 ( 6 ) of the third indent of Regulation ( EC ) No 800 / 1999 and with the authorisation referred to in Article 17 ( 1 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 , in accordance with the model set out in Part D of Annex IX to this Regulation ;
( e ) the quantities broken down in accordance with KN ’ -@ codes or codes of the export refund nomenclature for milk products for which final licences have been granted in accordance with Articles 18 and 20 of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 and no refund has been requested , in accordance with the model in Part E of Annex IX to this Regulation .
Article 12
Member States shall notify the Commission , before the 16th of each month n @ 4 , of the quantities broken down by KN @ codes and identification codes for which the formalities for export have been completed without refund , in accordance with the model set out in Part A of Annex X to this Regulation .
Article 13
Member States notify the Commission before 16 July of the previous GATT @ year :
( a ) the quantities for which the application of Article 5 ( 3 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 174 / 1999 has been approved and , where this leads to a difference in the reimbursement rate granted , stating the refund rate and the code of the export refund nomenclature for milk products and the code of export refund nomenclature for the product actually exported , in accordance with the model set out in Part B of Annex X to this Regulation ;
( b ) the quantities broken down by codes of the export refund nomenclature for milk products to which Article 18 ( 3 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 800 / 1999 has been applied , provided that the refund rate actually applied differs from the rate specified in the licence , stating the difference between the refund for the provision specified in the licence and the refund actually granted , in accordance with the model in Part C of Annex X to this Regulation .
Chapter V
general AND CONCLUSIONS
Article 14
Member States shall provide the Commission with the information required by this Regulation on the basis of the means of communication listed in Annex XI .
Article 15
the Commission shall keep at its disposal the information provided by the Member States .
Article 16
Regulation ( EC ) No 1498 / 1999 is repealed .
Regulation ( EC ) No 1498 / 1999 remains valid for the transmission of information on the period before the start of the application of this Regulation .
References to the repealed Regulation shall be regarded as references to this Regulation and shall be read in Annex XIII in accordance with the table of conformity .
Article 17
this Regulation shall enter into force on the seventh day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union .
it will be valid from 1 July 2005 .
However , Article 6 ( 3 ) shall apply from 31 May 2005 .
this Regulation is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
