Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 570 / 2005
of 14 April 2005
amending Regulation ( EC ) No 118 / 2005 as regards the setting of ceilings for direct payments to be granted in accordance with Article 71 of Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1782 / 2003
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Considering the following reasons :
( 1 ) Annex IV to Regulation ( EC ) No 118 / 2005 amending Annex VIII to Regulation ( EC ) No 1782 / 2003 and setting the ceilings provided for in this Regulation for partial or optional implementation and the annual financial framework for the single area payment scheme provided for therein shall set the ceilings for direct payments to be granted in accordance with Article 71 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1782 / 2003 for the calendar year 2005 .
( 2 ) France has recently noted , when calculating the payment claims , that there is a significant deviation between the financial result of the use of the respective physical data on the various direct payments granted during the reference period , on the basis of which the reference amounts are determined , and the data transmitted by France , on the basis of which the ceilings for the various direct payments were set in Regulation ( EC ) No 118 / 2005 .
( 3 ) The ceilings applicable to direct payments in France in 2005 laid down in Regulation ( EC ) No 118 / 2005 shall therefore be amended .
( 4 ) Regulation ( EC ) No 118 / 2005 shall therefore be amended accordingly .
( 5 ) The measures provided for in this Regulation shall comply with the opinion of the Administrative Committee on Direct Payments ;
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
Annex IV to Regulation ( EC ) No 118 / 2005 receives the version of the annex to this Regulation .
Article 2
this Regulation shall enter into force on the day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union .
this Regulation is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 571 / 2005
of 14 April 2005
to set representative prices and additional import duties for molasses in the sugar sector from 15 April 2005
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Having regard to Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1260 / 2001 of 19 June 2001 on the common organisation of the market in sugar &#91; 1 &#93; , and in particular Article 24 ( 4 ) thereof ,
Considering the following reasons :
( 1 ) In accordance with Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 1422 / 95 of 23 June 1995 laying down implementing provisions for the import of molasses into the sugar sector and amending Regulation ( EEC ) No 785 / 68 &#91; 2 &#93; , the price of imports of molasses shall be determined in accordance with Commission Regulation ( EEC ) No 785 / 68 &#91; 3 &#93; and shall be deemed to be a &quot; representative price . &quot;
this price applies to standard quality in accordance with Article 1 of Regulation ( EEC ) No 785 / 68 .
2 . When determining representative prices , all information must be taken into account in accordance with Article 3 of Regulation ( EEC ) No 785 / 68 , with the exception of cases in accordance with Article 4 of that Regulation and , where appropriate , the definition may also take place in accordance with the procedure laid down in Article 7 of Regulation ( EEC ) No 785 / 68 .
( 3 ) In the case of quality other than standard , the price shall be increased or reduced depending on the quality of the molasses offered in application of Article 6 of Regulation ( EEC ) No 785 / 68 .
4 . If there is a difference between the trigger price for the product in question and the representative price , additional import duties shall be set in accordance with Article 3 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1422 / 95 .
in the event of suspension of import duties in accordance with Article 5 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1422 / 95 , special amounts shall be set for these duties .
The representative prices and additional duties on imports of the products concerned shall be set in accordance with Article 1 ( 2 ) and Article 3 ( 1 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1422 / 95 .
( 6 ) The measures provided for in this Regulation shall comply with the opinion of the Management Committee on Sugar ;
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
representative prices and additional duties on imports of the products of Article 1 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1422 / 95 are set out in the Annex .
Article 2
this Regulation enters into force on 15 April 2005 .
this Regulation is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 572 / 2005
of 14 April 2005
to set export refunds for white sugar and raw sugar in unchanged condition
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Having regard to Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1260 / 2001 of 19 June 2001 on the common organisation of the market in sugar &#91; 1 &#93; , and in particular Article 27 ( 5 ) ,
Considering the following reasons :
1 . Pursuant to Article 27 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1260 / 2001 , the difference between quotations or prices on the world market of the products referred to in Article 1 ( 1 ) ( a ) of the Regulation and the prices of these products in the Community may be compensated by a refund on export .
2 . In accordance with Regulation ( EC ) No 1260 / 2001 , reimbursements for white sugar and raw sugar not denatured and in unchanged condition shall be fixed , taking into account the situation on the Community market and on the world sugar market , and in particular the prices and cost elements referred to in Article 28 of the Regulation .
according to the same article , the economic aspects of the intended export must also be taken into account .
( 3 ) For raw sugar , the refund for the standard quality must be set .
this has been laid down in Annex I , point II of Regulation ( EC ) No 1260 / 2001 .
This refund shall also be laid down in accordance with Article 28 ( 4 ) of this Regulation .
Kandiszucker was defined in Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 2135 / 95 of 7 September 1995 laying down implementing rules for the granting of export refunds in the sugar sector &#91; 2 &#93; .
the reimbursement thus calculated must apply to the flavoured or coloured sugar for its sucrose content and must therefore be set for 1 % of this content .
( 4 ) In special cases , the refund amount may be determined by acts of a different nature .
( 5 ) The refund shall be set every two weeks .
it can be changed in the meantime .
6 . Pursuant to the first subparagraph of Article 27 ( 5 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1260 / 2001 , the situation on the world market or the specific requirements of certain markets may make it necessary to determine the reimbursement of the products referred to in Article 1 of the same Regulation differently depending on the objective .
( 7 ) The significant and rapid increase in preferential sugar imports from the countries of the Western Balkans since the beginning of 2001 and Community sugar exports to these countries seems to be highly artificial .
( 8 ) In order to avoid any abuse in the re-import into the Community of sugar products for which an export refund has been granted , it is advisable not to set a refund for the countries of the Western Balkans for the products covered by this Regulation .
( 9 ) Due to these factors and the current market situation in the sugar sector , in particular quotations and prices for sugar in the Community and on the world market , appropriate reimbursement amounts shall be set .
( 10 ) The measures provided for in this Regulation shall comply with the opinion of the Management Committee on Sugar ;
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
the export refunds in unchanged condition of the products referred to in Article 1 ( 1 ) ( a ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1260 / 2001 and not denatured shall be determined as indicated in the Annex .
Article 2
this Regulation enters into force on 15 April 2005 .
this Regulation is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
