Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 574 / 2005
of 14 April 2005
to set export refunds for milk and dairy products
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Having regard to Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 of 17 May 1999 on the common organisation of the market in milk and milk products &#91; 1 &#93; , and in particular Article 31 ( 3 ) thereof ,
Considering the following reasons :
1 . Pursuant to Article 31 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 , the difference between the prices of the products listed in Article 1 of the Regulation and the prices of these products in the Community may be compensated by a refund on export without exceeding the limits arising from the agreements concluded under Article 300 of the Treaty .
2 . Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 requires reimbursements for products exported in unamended condition referred to in Article 1 of the same Regulation , taking into account the following factors :
- the situation and expected development of prices for milk and dairy products and available quantities on the Community market , as well as prices for milk and milk products in international trade ,
- the marketing costs and the lowest cost of transporting Community markets to Community export ports or other export locations and the pre-accession costs to the country of destination ,
- the objectives of the common organisation of the market in milk and milk products , which are intended to ensure these markets a balanced situation and a natural development in prices and trade ,
- the restrictions arising from the agreements concluded under Article 300 of the Treaty ,
- the need to prevent disruptions to the Community market ,
- the economic aspect of the intended exports .
3 . Pursuant to Article 31 ( 5 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 , prices in the Community shall be determined taking into account the best actual prices in terms of export .
( a ) actual prices on the markets of the third countries ;
( b ) the lowest import prices in the third countries of destination when importing from third countries ;
( c ) producer prices established in the third countries exporting , taking into account , where appropriate , the subsidies granted by those countries ;
d ) the offer prices free border of the Community .
4 . Pursuant to Article 31 ( 3 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 , the situation in international trade or the specific requirements of certain markets may make it necessary to determine the reimbursement of the products referred to in Article 1 of the same Regulation at different levels depending on the provision or area of destination .
( 5 ) Article 31 ( 3 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 provides that the list of products for which a refund is granted on export and the amount of this refund shall be redetermined at least every four weeks , but the refund amount may be maintained unchanged for a period exceeding four weeks .
( 7 ) Commission Regulation ( EEC ) No 896 / 84 &#91; 4 &#93; provides for supplementary provisions for the granting of refunds when changing the marketing year , which concern the possible different fixing of refunds in accordance with the date of manufacture of the products .
( 8 ) In order to calculate the reimbursement for the types of melting cheese , it shall be envisaged that , if casein and / or caseinate are added , the quantity concerned shall not be taken into account .
9 . The application of these modalities to the current situation of the markets for milk and milk products and , in particular , to the prices of these products in the Community and in international trade shall lead to the fixing of the reimbursement for the products to the amounts referred to in the Annex to this Regulation .
( 10 ) The Management Committee on Milk and Milk Products has not given its opinion within the time limit set by its Chairman ,
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
the export refunds for exported products in unchanged condition referred to in Article 31 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 shall be set at the amounts reflected in the Annex .
Article 2
this Regulation enters into force on 15 April 2005 .
this Regulation is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
