Considering the following reasons :
Procedure
( 1 ) With Regulation ( EC ) No 206 / 2005 &#91; 3 &#93; ( hereinafter referred to as the &quot; Final Regulation &quot; ) , the Commission introduced final safeguards on 4 February 2005 .
One of the measures provided for in Article 2 of this Regulation is the application of a minimum import price ( abbreviated as &quot; MEP &quot; below ) .
The MEP in force until 15 April 2005 is laid down in Article 2 ( 3 ) of the final Regulation .
( 3 ) According to recital 112 of the final Regulation , an early review of the measures shall be carried out in justified cases before an adapted MEP enters into force .
( 4 ) In accordance with recital 112 , the Commission is currently monitoring the market and the development of prices .
The Commission has not yet been able to draw a conclusion from its observations on the adequacy of the final minimum import price .
in order to enable the Commission to reach a final conclusion but at the same time to avoid an unnecessary disruption to the market , it is considered appropriate in these circumstances to extend the start-up phase until 24 May 2005 -
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
only article
( 1 ) Article 2 ( 3 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 206 / 2005 replaces the date &quot; 15 April 2005 &quot; with the date &quot; 24 May 2005 &quot; .
( 2 ) Article 2 ( 4 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 206 / 2005 replaces the date &quot; 16 April 2005 &quot; with the date &quot; 25 May 2005 &quot; .
this Regulation shall enter into force on the day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union .
this Regulation is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
