Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 588 / 2005
of 15 April 2005
amending Regulation ( EC ) No 1002 / 2004 adopting commitments relating to the anti-dumping procedure concerning imports of potassium chloride originating in the Republic of Belarus , the Russian Federation and Ukraine
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Having regard to Council Regulation ( EC ) No 384 / 96 of 22 December 1995 on the protection against dumped imports from non-European Community countries &#91; 1 &#93; ( hereinafter referred to as the &quot; Basic Regulation &quot; ) , in particular Article 8 thereof ,
Having regard to Council Regulation ( EC ) No 992 / 2004 of 17 May 2004 amending Regulation ( EEC ) No 3068 / 92 establishing a final anti-dumping duty on imports of potassium chloride originating in Belarus , Russia and Ukraine &#91; 2 &#93; , in particular Article 1 thereof ,
after consultations in the Advisory Committee ,
Considering the following reasons :
( 1 ) The Council introduced Regulation ( EEC ) No 3068 / 92 &#91; 3 &#93; , a final anti-dumping duty on imports of potassium chloride originating in , inter alia , the Russian Federation ( hereinafter referred to as &quot; Russia &quot; ) .
by Regulation ( EC ) No 969 / 2000 &#91; 4 &#93; , the Council amended the measures originally introduced by Regulation ( EEC ) No 3068 / 92 on imports of potassium chloride originating in , inter alia , Russia and extended their validity .
( 2 ) In March 2004 , by means of a notice published in the Official Journal of the European Union &#91; 5 &#93; , the Commission itself initiated a partial interim review of measures relating to imports of potassium chloride originating in , inter alia , Russia in order to examine whether the measures had to be changed to 25 Member States ( hereinafter referred to as &apos; enlargement &apos; ) as a result of the enlargement of the European Union .
( 3 ) According to the results of this partial interim review , a temporary adaptation of the existing measures was in the interests of the Community in order to prevent sudden and excessively negative effects on importers and users in the ten new Member States of the European Union ( hereinafter referred to as &quot; EU @ 10 &quot; ) immediately after enlargement .
( 4 ) With Regulation ( EC ) No 992 / 2004 , the Council authorised the Commission to adopt commitments meeting the conditions laid down in paragraphs 27 to 32 of that Regulation .
on this basis , the Commission adopted commitments from two exporting manufacturers in Russia in accordance with Article 8 , Article 11 ( 3 ) , Article 21 and Article 22 ( c ) of the basic regulation by Regulation ( EC ) No 1002 / 2004 &#91; 6 &#93; .
( 5 ) In the case of an executive manufacturer , the Commission adopted a joint commitment offer for imports of potassium chloride produced by JSC Uralkali , Berezniki , Russia , and sold exclusively to the Community by Fertexim Ltd , Limassol , Cyprus .
( 6 ) JSC Uralkali informed the Commission that it would henceforth process its sales to the Community through another company called Uralkali Trading SA , Geneva , Switzerland .
therefore JSC Uralkali and Fertexim Ltd requested a corresponding amendment to Regulation ( EC ) No 1002 / 2004 on the adoption of the joint commitment offer .
To this end , JSC Uralkali and Uralkali Trading SA have jointly submitted a revised commitment offer .
( 7 ) JSC Uralkali also pointed out that the obligation adopted by Regulation ( EC ) No 1002 / 2004 did not allow direct sales of JSC Uralkali to independent customers in the Community .
In the revised commitment offer , JSC Uralkali also undertakes to comply with its conditions for direct sales to the Community .
( 8 ) The Commission examined the commitment offer .
it concluded that the revised commitment offer met all the conditions laid down in Regulation ( EC ) No 992 / 2004 , namely that i set the selling prices at a level that effectively contributes to the elimination of the damage , ii companies comply with certain import quantities for sales to customers in the EU and iii they also essentially retain their traditional sales patterns vis-à-vis individual customers in the EU .
Furthermore , it was concluded that , as claimed by JSC Uralkali , the transfer of Fertexim Ltd &apos;s distribution activities to Uralkali Trading SA did not affect the effectiveness of the obligation or , according to the information provided by the companies , their effective monitoring .
( 9 ) The JSC Uralkalis application for exemption of its direct sales to the Community from anti-dumping duties was considered acceptable as it complies with the usual procedure of adopting proper commitments from manufacturers directly exporting to the Community .
( 10 ) In the light of the foregoing , it was considered necessary to amend the part of Regulation ( EC ) No 1002 / 2004 accordingly ,
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
Article 1 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1002 / 2004 shall be replaced by the following :
&quot; Article 1
the commitments made by the following exporting manufacturers in connection with the anti-dumping procedure concerning imports of potassium chloride originating in the Republic of Belarus and the Russian Federation are adopted .
Country _ BAR _ Company _ BAR _ TARIC • -@ Additional code _ BAR _
Republic of Belarus _ BAR _ Republican Unitary Enterprise Production Amalgamation Belaruskali , Soligorsk , Belarus ( manufacturing ) and JSC International Potash Company , Moscow , Russia , or Belurs Handelsgesellschaft mbH , Vienna , Austria , or UAB Baltkalis , Vilnius , Lithuania ( sale to the first independent customer in the Community acting as importer ) _ BAR _ A518 _ BAR _
Russian Federation _ BAR _ JSC Silvinit , Solikamsk , Russia ( manufacturing ) and JSC International Potash Company , Moscow , Russia , or Belurs Handelsgesellschaft mbH , Vienna , Austria ( sale to the first independent customer in the community acting as importer ) _ BAR _ A519 _ BAR _
Russian Federation _ BAR _ JSC Uralkali , Berezniki , Russia ( manufacture and sale ) or JSC Uralkali , Berezniki , Russia ( manufacture ) and Uralkali Trading SA , Geneva , Switzerland ( sale to the first independent customer in the community acting as importer ) _ BAR _ A520 &quot; _ BAR _
Article 2
this Regulation shall enter into force on the day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union .
it is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
