COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Having regard to Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1255 / 1999 of 17 May 1999 on the common organisation of the market in milk and milk products &#91; 1 &#93; , and in particular Article 10 thereof ,
Considering the following reasons :
( 1 ) In accordance with Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 2571 / 97 of 15 December 1997 on the sale of cheap butter and the granting of aid for cream , butter and butter fat for the production of baked goods , ice cream and other foodstuffs &#91; 2 &#93; , the intervention bodies shall sell certain amounts of intervention butter from their stocks by tender and grant aid for the cream , butter and butter fat .
Article 18 of this Regulation establishes a minimum selling price for butter and a maximum aid amount for cream , butter and butter fat on the basis of the offers received on each individual tender , or it is decided not to comply with the invitation to tender .
the stated minimum selling price and the maximum amount of aid in question can be differentiated depending on the purpose , milk fat content of the butter and processing method .
the amount of processing reliability ( s ) must be determined accordingly .
