Considering the following reasons :
( 1 ) Article 2 of Regulation ( EC ) No 2771 / 1999 provides that , depending on the case , the Commission shall open or suspend purchases in a Member State as soon as it is established that the market price in the Member State concerned is below 92 % of the intervention price for two consecutive weeks or corresponds to at least 92 % of the intervention price for two consecutive weeks .
( 2 ) The most recent list of Member States in which the intervention is suspended was drawn up by Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 544 / 2005 &#91; 3 &#93; .
this list must be adapted to take account of the new market prices notified by Sweden in accordance with Article 8 of Regulation ( EC ) No 2771 / 1999 .
