Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 595 / 2005
of 15 April 2005
to set tariffs in force in the cereals sector from 16 April 2005
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Having regard to Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1784 / 2003 of 29 September 2003 on the common organisation of the market in cereals &#91; 1 &#93; ,
Having regard to Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 1249 / 96 of 28 June 1996 laying down implementing provisions for the application of Council Regulation ( EEC ) No 1766 / 92 as regards customs duties applicable in the cereals sector &#91; 2 &#93; , in particular Article 2 ( 1 ) thereof ,
Considering the following reasons :
1 . Pursuant to Article 10 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1784 / 2003 , the customs duties of the common customs tariff shall be levied on the import of the products referred to in Article 1 of the same Regulation .
However , in the case of the products referred to in paragraph 2 of the same Article , customs duties correspond to the intervention price applicable to their import , increased by 55 % and reduced by the price applicable to the delivery in question .
However , this rate must not exceed the common customs tariff .
2 . Pursuant to Article 10 ( 3 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1784 / 2003 , the cif @ import price shall be calculated on the basis of the representative world market prices applicable to the product in question .
( 3 ) Regulation ( EC ) No 1249 / 96 adopted implementing provisions relating to Regulation ( EC ) No 1784 / 2003 concerning customs duties in the cereals sector .
( 4 ) Import duties shall apply until a redefinition enters into force .
( 5 ) In order for import duties to be applied smoothly , their calculation should be based on the market prices determined in representative reference periods .
( 6 ) The application of Regulation ( EC ) No 1249 / 96 shall result in the fixing of customs duties in accordance with Annex I to this Regulation ;
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
the duties applicable in the cereals sector in accordance with Article 10 ( 2 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1784 / 2003 are laid down in Annex I to this Regulation on the basis of the components specified in Annex II .
Article 2
this Regulation enters into force on 16 April 2005 .
this Regulation is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
