Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 600 / 2005
of 18 April 2005
on the re-authorisation of a coccidiostatic drug as an additive in feed for ten years , the provisional authorisation of an additive and the authorisation of certain additives in feed for an indefinite period of time
( Text of importance for the EEA )
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Having regard to Council Directive 70 / 524 / EEC of 23 November 1970 on additives in animal nutrition &#91; 1 &#93; , and in particular Articles 3 and 9d ( 1 ) and 9e ( 1 ) thereof ,
Having regard to Regulation ( EC ) No 1831 / 2003 of the European Parliament and of the Council of 22 September 2003 on additives for use in animal nutrition &#91; 2 &#93; , in particular Article 25 thereof ,
Considering the following reasons :
( 1 ) Regulation ( EC ) No 1831 / 2003 provides for the authorisation of additives for use in animal nutrition .
( 2 ) Article 25 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1831 / 2003 lays down transitional measures for applications for authorisation of feed additives submitted under Directive 70 / 524 / EEC before the date from which Regulation ( EC ) No 1831 / 2003 applied .
3 . Applications for authorisation of the additives listed in the annexes to this Regulation were submitted before the date on which Regulation ( EC ) No 1831 / 2003 applied .
( 4 ) Initial comments on these requests have been sent to the Commission in accordance with Article 4 ( 4 ) of Directive 70 / 524 / EEC before the application date of Regulation ( EC ) No 1831 / 2003 .
These applications must therefore continue to be dealt with in accordance with Article 4 of Directive 70 / 524 / EEC .
5 . The person responsible for placing Salinomax 120G on the market submitted an application for authorisation of the coccidiostatic drug for broilers for ten years in accordance with Article 4 of this Directive .
the European Food Safety Authority ( EFSA ) has issued an opinion on the safe use of this preparation for humans , animals and the environment under the conditions set out in Annex I to this Regulation .
the assessment has shown that the conditions set out in Article 3a of Directive 70 / 524 / EEC for such authorisation are met .
the use of this preparation in accordance with Annex I should therefore be authorised for ten years .
( 6 ) Data was submitted to support an application for approval of the new additive Lactobacillus acidophilus DSM 13241 for dogs and cats .
On 15 April 2004 and 27 October 2004 , EFSA issued a favourable opinion on safety for target animal species , the user and the environment .
the assessment has shown that the conditions set out in Article 3a of Directive 70 / 524 / EEC for such authorisation are met .
the use of this microorganism – @ preparation according to Annex II should therefore be provisionally approved .
( 7 ) The use of the microorganism -@ preparation from Enterococcus faecium ( ATCC 53519 ) and Enterococcus faecium ( ATCC 55593 ) was provisionally authorised for broilers for the first time by Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 1436 / 98 &#91; 3 &#93; .
new data have been submitted to support an application for approval of this microorganism – @ preparation for an unlimited period of time .
the assessment has shown that the conditions set out in Article 3a of Directive 70 / 524 / EEC for such authorisation are met .
the use of this microorganism – @ preparation according to Annex III should therefore be approved for an unlimited period of time .
( 8 ) The use of the microorganism &amp; quot ; -@ preparation from Bacillus licheniformis ( DSM 5749 ) and Bacillus subtilis ( DSM 5750 ) was provisionally authorised for calves for the first time by Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 2437 / 2000 &#91; 4 &#93; and Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 418 / 2001 &#91; 5 &#93; .
new data have been submitted to support an application for approval of this microorganism – @ preparation for an unlimited period of time .
the assessment has shown that the conditions set out in Article 3a of Directive 70 / 524 / EEC for such authorisation are met .
the use of this microorganism – @ preparation according to Annex III should therefore be approved for an unlimited period of time .
( 9 ) The use of the microorganism -@ preparation from Saccharomyces cerevisiae ( NCYC Sc 47 ) was provisionally approved for rabbits for the first time by Regulation ( EC ) No 1436 / 98 .
new data have been submitted to support an application for approval of this microorganism – @ preparation for an unlimited period of time .
the assessment has shown that the conditions set out in Article 3a of Directive 70 / 524 / EEC for such authorisation are met .
the use of this microorganism – @ preparation according to Annex III should therefore be approved for an unlimited period of time .
10 . The evaluation of this request shall show that certain procedures should be prescribed to protect workers from exposure to the additive listed in the Annex .
appropriate safeguards should be ensured by applying Council Directive 89 / 391 / EEC of 12 June 1989 on the implementation of measures to improve the safety and health of workers at work &#91; 6 &#93; .
11 . The measures provided for in this Regulation are in line with the opinion of the Standing Committee on the Food Chain and Animal Health .
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
the preparation of the group &quot; coccidiostats and other medicinal products &quot; referred to in Annex I shall be authorised as an additive in animal nutrition for a period of ten years under the conditions listed in this Annex .
Article 2
the preparation of the Microorganisms group referred to in Annex II will be provisionally authorised as an additive in animal nutrition for four years under the conditions listed in this Annex .
Article 3
the preparations of the Microorganisms Group referred to in Annex III will be authorised as additives in feed for an unlimited period of time under the conditions set out in this Annex .
Article 4
this Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union .
it is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
