Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 605 / 2005
of 19 April 2005
amending Regulation ( EC ) No 296 / 96 on the information to be provided by Member States and on the monthly assumption of expenditure financed by the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund ( EAGGF ) , Guarantee Section
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Having regard to Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1258 / 1999 of 17 May 1999 on the financing of the common agricultural policy &#91; 1 &#93; , in particular Article 5 ( 3 ) and Article 7 ( 5 ) thereof ,
Considering the following reasons :
( 1 ) In accordance with Article 3 of Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 296 / 96 &#91; 2 &#93; , it shall be constantly informed at regular intervals of expenditure incurred by Member States .
to avoid unnecessary communications , it must be envisaged that this information must be transmitted monthly , without prejudice to the obligation of Member States to provide the Commission with information on a weekly basis in order to enable appropriate monitoring of expenditure development .
( 2 ) Certain information to be communicated by Member States should be transmitted electronically and digitally so that the Commission can use it directly for accounting .
nevertheless , in justified cases , transmission must remain possible in another way .
( 3 ) In order to simplify and streamline administrative procedures , the simultaneous transmission of a copy of this information in paper form should only be required for the monthly summaries .
( 4 ) In practice , the indication of certain quantities or areas in the detailed notification submitted by the Member States has little interest in granting the monthly advances .
this information should therefore be dispensed with .
( 5 ) The Commission &amp; apos ; s payments from the EAGGF Guarantee Section budget shall be made exclusively in euros .
Member States not participating in the euro , for their part , retain the choice between the euro and their national currency for payments to beneficiaries .
However , the paying agencies of these Member States , which make payments both in local currency and in euros , should be obliged to maintain separate accounts for the currencies used for payment .
in order to avoid a double conversion of payments , it is indicated that the possibility of reporting amounts paid in euros in local currency will be abolished .
6 . If , on the basis of Member States &amp; apos ; expenditure notifications , the sum of the commitments granted in anticipation , where appropriate , in accordance with Article 150 ( 3 ) of Council Regulation ( EC , Euratom ) No 1605 / 2002 of 25 June 2002 on the Financial Regulation for the general budget of the European Communities &#91; 3 &#93; exceeds half of the corresponding total budget for the current financial year , the Commission shall reduce these commitments .
in the interests of good budgetary management , this reduction should be proportionally distributed to all Member States on the basis of reported expenditure .
7 . If the Community budget has not yet been definitively established at the beginning of the financial year , payments may be made monthly per chapter up to one twelfth of the appropriations approved for the previous financial year in the relevant chapter in accordance with the second subparagraph of Article 13 ( 2 ) of Regulation ( EC , Euratom ) No 1605 / 2002 .
In order to allocate the available funds fairly among the Member States , it is advisable to ensure that , in this case , the advances are granted in the amount of one percentage of the expenditure reported by the individual Member States per chapter and that the remaining amount not taken over in the respective month is allocated again in the Commission &amp; apos ; s decisions on subsequent monthly payments .
( 8 ) Within the framework of the CAP -@ reform and the introduction of the Single Payment Scheme , compliance by Member States with payment deadlines is essential for the proper application of the rules of budgetary discipline .
relevant provisions should therefore be laid down to prevent as much as possible from exceeding the annual resources available in the Community budget .
( 9 ) If there are delays in transmitting the documents relating to payments under Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 817 / 2004 of 29 April 2004 laying down implementing provisions for Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1257 / 1999 on the promotion of rural development by the European Agricultural Guidance and Guarantee Fund ( EAGGF ) &#91; 4 &#93; , it should be possible for the purpose of proper administration to postpone payments to a Member State for the month of September to the following month .
( 10 ) Expenditure on material measures in warehousing carried out in the month of September will be paid 50 % in October and the balance in November .
in order to simplify accounting by the paying agencies , it must be envisaged that 100 % of the expenditure on these material measures will be covered in October .
( 11 ) Rural development expenditure co-financed by the Community budget and national budgets shall be reported to the beneficiary no later than the second month after payment .
to unify the accounting rules in the area of the EAGGF Guarantee Section , it is advisable to ensure that these expenses are reported for the month in which the payment was made to the beneficiary .
( 12 ) Regulation ( EC ) No 296 / 96 shall therefore be amended accordingly .
( 13 ) The measures provided for in this Regulation shall comply with the opinion of the EAGGF @ Committee -
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
Regulation ( EC ) No 296 / 96 is amended as follows :
1 . Article 3 shall be amended as follows :
( a ) paragraphs 1 , 2 and 3 shall be replaced by the following :
Member States shall collect information on the total amount of expenditure incurred each week and shall keep it available to the Commission .
they make available at the latest on the third working day of each week the information on the total amount of expenditure made from the beginning of the month until the end of the previous week .
if the week exceeds one end of the month , Member States will make available information on the total amount of expenditure incurred during the previous month no later than the third working day of the new month .
2 . Member States shall transmit electronically the information on the total amount of expenditure incurred in a month at the latest on the third working day of the following month , together with any information suitable for explaining significant discrepancies between the forecasts made in application of paragraph 5 and the actual expenditure .
3 . Member States shall notify the Commission electronically on a monthly basis no later than the 10th of each month of the total expenditure they have incurred in the previous month .
However , the communication on expenditure made between 1 and 15 October shall be forwarded no later than the 25th of the same month .
3a .
In sufficiently justified cases , the Commission may allow a different method of transmission to be used for the communications referred to in paragraphs 2 and 3 . &quot;
( b ) paragraph 5 shall be replaced by the following :
Member States shall transmit to the Commission on a monthly basis , electronically , no later than the 20th of each month , the documents for the expenditure to be covered by the Community budget in the previous month .
However , the documents for the assumption of expenditure from 1 to 15 October must be submitted no later than 10 November .
the summary of the information provided for in paragraph 6 ( b ) shall also be forwarded to the Commission in paper form . &quot;
( c ) paragraph 6 shall be replaced by the following :
I ) for letter a the third indent is deleted ;
II ) Letter b shall be replaced by the following :
&quot; ( b ) a summary of the information referred to in point ( a ) ; &quot;
( d ) paragraph 9 shall be replaced by the following :
The paying agencies of the Member States not participating in the euro must maintain separate accounting in the currency in which payments were made to the beneficiaries .
the same separation must be maintained for the notifications prepared during the clearance of accounts procedure . &quot;
2 . Article 4 shall be amended as follows :
( a ) paragraph 1 shall be replaced by the following :
&quot; 1 . Without prejudice to the provisions of Article 14 of Council Regulation ( EC ) No 2040 / 2000 &#91; 5 &#93; , the Commission shall decide and transfer the monthly advances on expenditure to be taken on the basis of the information provided in accordance with Article 3 .
If the early commitments under Article 150 ( 3 ) of Council Regulation ( EC , Euratom ) No 1605 / 2002 &#91; 6 &#93; exceed half of the corresponding total dotation of the current financial year , the advances will be granted in the amount of one percentage of the expenditure reported by the Member States .
the Commission shall take into account the balance not granted to Member States in its decisions on subsequent refunds .
If the Community budget has not yet been finalised at the beginning of the financial year , advances will be granted in the amount of a percentage of the expenditure reported by the Member States , which will be set per expenditure capital and in compliance with the ceilings laid down in Article 13 of Regulation ( EC , Euratom ) No 1605 / 2002 .
the Commission shall take into account the balance not granted to Member States in its decisions on subsequent refunds .
( b ) paragraph 2 shall be replaced by the following :
&quot; 2 . All expenses incurred outside the prescribed dates and deadlines shall only be partially covered under the advance scheme in accordance with the following rules :
( a ) No reduction shall be made for up to 4 % of expenditure on time or on time ;
( b ) after claiming the margin of 4 % , the additional late expenditure will be reduced as follows :
- exceeding up to one month : by 10 % ,
- exceeding up to two months : by 25 % ,
- exceeding up to three months : by 45 % ,
- exceeding up to four months : by 70 % ,
- exceeding up to five months or more : 100 % .
( c ) However , the following applies to direct payments within the meaning of Article 12 , Title III or , where appropriate , Title IVa of Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1782 / 2003 &#91; 7 &#93; made for year N , which are carried out outside the prescribed dates and deadlines after 15 October of N + 1 :
- If the margin of 4 % provided for in point ( a ) has not been fully used for payments made no later than 15 October of the year N + 1 and the remaining part of the margin is more than 2 % , it will be reduced to 2 % ;
- after claiming the above margins , the expenditure covered by these letters will be reduced by 100 % .
( d ) If specific circumstances arise in the management of certain measures or if coherent justifications are provided by the Member States , the Commission shall apply a different staggering and / or lower reduction percentages or the percentage of &apos; zero &apos; .
However , for payments covered by point ( c ) , the above rate shall apply within the limits set out in the second indent of point ( c ) .
( e ) The cuts referred to in this Article shall be made in compliance with the provisions of Article 14 of Regulation ( EC ) No 2040 / 2000 .
( c ) paragraph 6 shall be replaced by the following :
&quot; 6 . If the documents referred to in Article 55 ( 1 ) of Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 817 / 2004 &#91; 9 &#93; have not been received by the Commission by 30 September of each year , the Commission may , after informing the Member State concerned , suspend the payment of the advance for the expenditure incurred in September under the aforementioned Regulation until the advance payment for the expenditure of the month of October .
3 . Article 5 ( 2 ) shall be replaced by the following :
&quot; 2 . The expenditure referred to in paragraph 1 shall be recorded by the paying agencies during the month following the month in which the substantive measures were carried out .
in the monthly final accounts , the material measures from the beginning of the financial year to the end of the month in question must be taken into account .
However , the expenditure on the material measures carried out in September will be recorded by the paying agencies no later than 15 October . &quot;
4 . Article 7 ( 1 ) ( b ) shall be deleted .
Article 2
this Regulation shall enter into force on the twentieth day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union .
it shall apply from 16 October 2005 , with the exception of Article 1 ( 1 ) ( d ) and ( 4 ) , which shall apply from 16 October 2006 .
this Regulation is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 606 / 2005
of 19 April 2005
amending Regulation ( EC ) No 795 / 2004 laying down implementing provisions on the Single Payment Scheme in accordance with Council Regulation ( EC ) No 1782 / 2003 laying down common rules for direct payments under the common agricultural policy and certain support schemes for farmers
COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES
Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community ,
Considering the following reasons :
( 1 ) Commission Regulation ( EC ) No 795 / 2004 &#91; 2 &#93; lays down the implementing provisions of the Single Payment Scheme , which have been in force since the beginning of 2005 .
in the administrative and operational implementation of the scheme at national level , it has been shown that it is necessary to adopt further implementing provisions on some aspects of the scheme and to clarify and adapt the existing provisions on some points .
2 . Pursuant to Article 24 ( 2 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 795 / 2004 , Member States shall set the start of the 10 ° -@ month ° -@ deadline laid down in Article 44 ( 3 ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1782 / 2003 for each individual proprietor at a single date , which shall be determined within a calendar year preceding the year of filing an application for participation in the Single Payment Scheme between 1 September and 30 April of the following calendar year , or shall leave it to the proprietor to determine the start within the specified period .
if there are special conditions in agriculture , the farmers should have more room for manoeuvre in determining the start of the 10 ° @ month ° -@ deadline for the individual plots .
( 3 ) In accordance with Article 51 of Regulation ( EC ) No 1782 / 2003 , amended by Council Regulation ( EC ) No 864 / 2004 &#91; 3 &#93; and applicable under Regulation ( EC ) No 394 / 2005 since 1 January 2005 , Member States may allow secondary crops to be cultivated on eligible areas for a maximum period of three months starting on 15 August each year .
However , this date should be brought forward in order to allow temporary cultivation of vegetables in regions where cereals are usually harvested earlier for climatic reasons in accordance with Member States &amp; apos ; communications to the Commission .
( 4 ) Regulation ( EC ) No 795 / 2004 shall therefore be amended accordingly .
( 5 ) As Regulation ( EC ) No 795 / 2004 has been in force since 1 January 2005 , this Regulation should apply retroactively from that date .
( 6 ) The measures provided for in this Regulation are in line with the opinion of the Administrative Committee on Direct Payments ;
has FOLLOWING REGULATION :
Article 1
Regulation ( EC ) No 795 / 2004 is amended as follows :
1 . The following subparagraph shall be added to Article 24 ( 2 ) :
&quot; If there are specific conditions in agriculture , however , a Member State may allow farmers to set the start of the 10 ° @ month ° -@ period on their farm at two different times within the specified period in accordance with the first subparagraph .
Farm owners making use of this option state in their collective application their choice for each individual plot in addition to the information to be provided in accordance with Article 12 of Regulation ( EC ) No 796 / 2004 . &quot;
2 . The following Article 28a is inserted :
&quot; Article 28a
three ° -@ month ° -@ period pursuant to Article 51 ( b ) of Regulation ( EC ) No 1782 / 2003
the Member States listed in the Annex may allow secondary crops to be cultivated on the eligible hectares for a period not exceeding three months , starting each year on the date indicated for them in the Annex . &quot;
3 . The text annexed to this Regulation shall be added as an annex .
Article 2
this Regulation shall enter into force on the date of its publication in the Official Journal of the European Union .
it shall apply with effect from 1 January 2005 .
this Regulation is binding in all its parts and applies directly in each Member State .
